	     London - A British camera operator has died on the set of the BBC/Netflix miniseries "The Forgiving Earth." Agent Sarah Prince says Mark Milsome died in Ghana over the weekend while filming a night-time stunt sequence for the thriller. She said on Monday that an investigation is underway. Prince says Milsome was "an incredibly humble and talented man. ... We are all devastated by his loss." Milsome was 54 and had worked on TV series including "Sherlock" and "Game of Thrones" and films including "Saving Private Ryan" and "Quantum of Solace." The BBC said he was a "hugely talented and a much respected colleague." The broadcaster said it was "deeply shocked and saddened." Written by Hugo Blick, the war-crimes thriller is due to be broadcast by the BBC in Britain and Netflix elsewhere. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  